com.yahoo.bullet.typesystem

Enum Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Type>
      • com.yahoo.bullet.typesystem.Type
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Type>

    public enum Type
extends Enum<Type>
    Stores the various types that can be understood by the type system in Bullet.

      • getType

        public static Type getType(Object object)
        Tries to get the type of a given object. If the object is a complex or composite type, then it must contain at least one value that also satisfies this property if it too is a complex type. If not, the whole type is derived to be UNKNOWN and not LISTS of UNKNOWN or MAPS of UNKNOWN. Note that if the object is a composite type that contains multiple different types of values, any one of them maybe used to determine the type leading to undefined behavior. It might be possible to create such a composite object and then use forceCast(Type, Type, Serializable) to force this object to a desired type if the cast can be done (even with loss of precision).
        Parameters:
        object - The object whose type is to be determined.
        Returns:
        Type for this object, the NULL if the object was null or UNKNOWN if the type could not be determined.

      • cast

        public Serializable cast(Serializable object)
        Takes an object and casts it to this type. Follows widening conventions for primitive numeric data. For all other data, if the cast cannot be done safely, this will throw an instance RuntimeException. See forceCast(Type, Serializable) to force type changes when the cast cannot be done naturally.
        Parameters:
        object - The object that is being cast.
        Returns:
        The casted Serializable object.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if the cast cannot be done safely.

      • forceCast

        public Serializable forceCast(Type castedType,
                              Serializable object)
        Attempt to force cast the Serializable object of this Type type to the given Type castedType. Follows widening conventions for primitive numeric data, including within maps and lists. However, types will be forced with possible loss of precision or data in other cases that can be done. Otherwise, the cast will fail with a RuntimeException when it is not possible to cast at all. See cast(Serializable) if you are only interested in performing safe casts. Note that maps will be casted to HashMap and lists will be casted to ArrayList.
        Parameters:
        castedType - The Type to be casted to.
        object - The object to be casted.
        Returns:
        The Serializable result of the cast.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if the cast cannot be done.

        public static boolean canForceCast(Type finalType,
